The England cricket team 's involvement with multi-billion-pound fraudster Allen Stanford -- has been defended by West Indies cricket legend Sir Curtly Ambrose .
Great fast bowler Ambrose was one of the West Indies stars , along with Sir Viv Richards and Richie Richardson , who accompanied Stanford when he flew by helicopter to the Lord 's nursery ground in 2008 to launch his five-year deal with England .
Stanford 's deal ended with his arrest and subsequent 110-year jail sentence .